upcoming.name: Flutter Tutorials Session & Firebase Study Jam '20
upcoming.description:
- The Flutter tutorials Session teaches you how to use the Flutter framework to build mobile applications for iOS and Android.
- Firebase is Google’s mobile app development platform for iOS, Android, and mobile web developers. Firebase gives you functionality like analytics, databases, messaging and crash reporting so you can move quickly and focus on your users.

Choose from the following:

Building layouts
How to build layouts using Flutter’s layout mechanism. Once you’ve learned basic principles, you’ll build the layout for a sample screenshot.
Adding interactivity to your Flutter app
You’ll extend the simple layout app created in “Building Layouts in Flutter” to make an icon tappable. Different ways of managing a widget’s state are also discussed.
Animations in Flutter
Explains the fundamental classes in the Flutter animation package (controllers, Animatable, curves, listeners, builders), as it guides you through a progression of tween animations using different aspects of the animation APIs.

upcoming.name: Google Cloud Next '20 Extended & Cloud Study Jam '20
upcoming.description:
First Cloud Next Extended event on the May 18 at IUHD.

We will learn together about the most exciting announcements of Google Cloud Next 2020, and follow with a Cloud Study Jam - a community-run study group for developers where we'll be taking on:
- From containerizing applications to data engineering, our Study Jam Bootcamp can be tailored to specific Cloud topics and skill levels. Whether you’re a beginner developer or interested in diving into Machine Learning, Kubernetes, Certification, IoT, or Security, there’s a track for you. Get official hands-on technical training at no cost, on a wide range of technologies and topics.

upcoming.name: Machine Learning Study Jam
upcoming.description:
Machine Learning Study Jam is a great opportunity to bring members of the community together to learn something new or advance their knowledge, with the help of a community facilitator. Skills learned in this workshop can be used for personal development or career advancement. The Machine Learning Study Jam would bring together a small group of members who are interested in learning about Machine Learning Crash. Join us for a Machine Learning Study Jam where we will be talking about Machine Learning basics to deployment!

This event is intended for those who wish to learn about ML from a practical, applied perspective that will enable you to use machine learning in your everyday projects and learn about the power of solutions provided by Google Cloud to help you with Machine Learning. This is also a great opportunity for anyone with basic technical knowledge and limited Machine Learning knowledge willing to gain some practical experience in ML.
